members.doc: Delete only the portion of the word to the left/right of cursor if we’re in the middle of a word.
members.name: word_ends

members.doc: Delete display-lines. Display-lines refers to the visible lines, with respect to to the current line breaks. As opposed to paragraphs, which are defined by line breaks in the input.
members.name: display_lines

members.doc: Delete only the portion of the display-line to the left/right of cursor.
members.name: display_line_ends

members.doc: Delete to the end of the paragraph. Like C-k in Emacs (or its reverse).
members.name: paragraph_ends

members.doc: Delete entire line. Like C-k in pico.
members.name: paragraphs

members.doc: Delete only whitespace. Like M-\ in Emacs.
members.name: whitespace
